Value_App

TC doing itThingDefinitionDoc
PI-Climateclim_SW_periodic_onMakers_pertinence(check_freq_mins=5, not_used_hours=13, open_duration_mins=4, C_ok_diff=-0.001)Activates the on/off valves clim_SW regularly to ensure they keep functioning.
The script also tests the valve measuring its temperature against the producer.
"not_used_hours": 13, time in hours that when a Clim_SW is not used it will run for a short time to
keep the mechanics working regularly
"check_freq_mins": 5, timer in minutes that is looked for a Clim_SW not being used a while
"open_duration_mins": 4, time in minutes that the Clim_SW is forced open, should be less than
pump_duration_min
"C_ok_diff": 1.5, at the end of the run to test for good working of Clim_SW, the minumum
temperature difference of the Clim_SW sensor before and after activation
PI-Climategas_heaterBoiler_on_off(max_boiler_nr_rooms=6, C_boiler_highest=70, C_boiler_lowest=40, C_boiler_threshold=4, C_outside_max_boiler=-5, C_outside_min_boiler=15)Calculates the boiler range temperature based on the outside temperature and the arguments of this function
and determines to switch on or off the boiler.
"max_boiler_nr_rooms": 6, if these number of rooms need heating then the boiler temp is increased
to its max setting...
"C_boiler_highest": 65, highest boiler temperature, when all of heating is needed
"C_boiler_lowest": 35, lowest boiler temperature, when little heating is needed
"C_boiler_threshold": 4, value under/above then boiler is on/off, so range is double this
"C_outside_max_boiler": -5, outside low low temperature, all of warming needed
"C_outside_min_boiler": 15, outside high temperature, little warming needed

via parent method_things :
"C_in": Sensor(path="..",i_read="°C"), boiler incoming water temp
"C_out": Sensor(path="..",i_read="°C") boiler outgoing water temp

returns True/False if the boiler has to be switched on/off
PI-ClimatepumpPump_speed_set(act_run_idle_hours=13, max_speed_active_makers=60, speed_act_run=50, speed_lowest=50)Calculates the optimal pump speed based on the number of clim_SW that are active and the clim_SP ones.
"speed_lowest": 50, minimum speed of the pump in percent,
"max_speed_active_makers": 60, percent of active clim_makers to reach full pump power
"act_run_idle_hours": 13, hours idle to shoot an activation run, !remember set duration
"speed_act_run": 50, speed when the pump is activated after not used for a while
returns pump_speed as a value between 0 and 100%
